37	 * OpenfpgaContext, which is used for data exchange between
38	 * different modules in OpenFPGA shell environment
39	 *
40	 * If a command of OpenFPGA needs to exchange data with other commands,
41	 * it must use this data structure to access/mutate.
42	 * In such case, you must add data structures to OpenfpgaContext
43	 *
44	 * Note:
45	 * Please respect to the following rules when using the OpenfpgaContext
46	 * 1. This data structure will be created only once in the main() function
47	 *    The data structure is design to be large and contain all the
48	 *    data structure required by each module of OpenFPGA core engine.
49	 *    Do NOT create or duplicate in your own module!
50	 * 2. Be clear in your mind if you want to access/mutate the data inside
51	 *OpenfpgaContext Read-only data should be accessed by const OpenfpgaContext&
52	 *    Mutate should use reference
53	 *      OpenfpgaContext&
54	 * 3. Please keep the definition of OpenfpgaContext short
55	 *    Do put ONLY well-modularized data structure under this root.
56	 * 4. We build this data structure based on the Context from VPR
57	 *    which does NOT allow users to copy the internal members
58	 *    This is due to that the data structures in the OpenFPGA context
59	 *    are typically big in terms of memory
